column4: Qty x 1 Lightning Diverter SKU EFD70309D Supplier Code 70309D
column9:
Lightning is the biggest destroyer of electric fences. Damage can come through the fence or your home mains, it can also happen when a storm is many kilometres away. The Daken Lightning Diverter aims to lessen and stop the damage that can happen to your energiser. Install in-line as close as possible to your energiser. If you are in a lightning prone area it is worthwhile considering installing more than one.
Protect energiser from lightning
Easy to install

column4: Qty x 1 BT2 SKU EFD70270D Supplier Code 70270D
column9:
Overview
Daken battery powered energiser's are the perfect partner for strip grazing, temporary fencing and remote applications. Will use a battery where mains power is not available. We supply small portable models to high power ones for bigger stations and long runs.
Specification
The Daken BT2 electric fence energiser is suitable for strip grazing and smaller fencing applications for up to 2km's of fence.
The compact BT2 is a short-range energiser that suits small jobs around your property or is a handy stand by. Even though itâ€™s an entry level electric fence energiser it still has a self-diagnostic ability to tell you if you have a short or if the battery is low and needs to be recharged. The Daken BT2 electric fence energiser is s practical and easy to use energiser that is strong, ant proof and weather proof.
  Quick specs
12Volt DC powered
Range up to 2km multi wire fence
Power 0.2 Stored Joules
Diagnostic Centre with, energiser OK, Overload, Low battery
Comes with two battery leads red and Black
Comes with fence red and earth green leads
3 Year Factory Warranty
Designed, Assembled, Tested and Serviced in Australia
  Battery Required:
A 12V Battery is not included with this energizer.
We do sell small low cost 12V 7.2AH Batteries that can be paired with this unit.
The 12V 7.2AH battery will last roughly 12 days before needing a charge.
12V Batteries with a larger â€œAHâ€, eg: 70ah (standard size car battery), 100ah or more will allow this unit to run for a number of weeks before requiring a recharge. 
Look after your battery, Keep in a plastic battery box or container to protect it from the weather, and where possible keep it off the ground to stop it from self-discharging.
Documents and Manuals
BT2, BT6, BT12 Installation and Operations Manual

column4: Qty x 1 MT60 SKU EFD70507D Supplier Code 70507D
column9:
Overview
Daken mains powered energisers are the preferred option for permanent fencing applications. Their low power consumption means they are cost effective to run. These energisers should be installed inside and out of the weather to ensure safety.
Specification
The Daken MT60 electric fence energiser is suitable for large permanent fencing applications and feral animal control for up to 60km's of fence.
The full size MT60 is a medium-range energiser that suits many permanent jobs around your property but with a bit extra power to overcome some fence leakage. This model has a half power terminal that can be used on training paddocks, and it can also be used for feral animal control with its Bi-Polar function. It also has an LCD display showing Output Voltage and Fence Load.
Quick specs
Mains Powered
Range up to 60km multi wire fence
Power 5.6 Stored Joules
Peak Output Voltage 8.8KV
Diagnostic Centre with LCD display Output voltage Load Factor, energiser OK, Overload, Low battery
Half Power Terminal
Bi-Polar or Conventional operation
3 Year Factory Warranty
Designed, Assembled, Tested and Serviced in Australia
Documents and Manuals
Daken Ag Installation manual MT BT

column9:
Nemteks wooden post intermediate insulator is fastened to your wooden posts and is used to secure the horse electric fence poly tape in place. It is only used on straight runs. The robust design secures the tape in place. White in colour for higher visibility to the horse.The horse now knows where the electric fence is situated and should tend to avoid it.This model is ideal for the wide 40 mm tape and although it can take the 20mm poly tape, it is recommended that the 20mm tape be used with our thick wire rope insulator which is another option to contain horses.

Features

• Heavy duty design construction to minimise risk of breakage • Soft blue rubber pads to secure poly tape, reducing wear and extending the life span of the tape.

Specifications

  • Bag of 25
  • Material: UV stabilised polyethylene
  • Rubber pad
  • Colour: White with blue

Specification
The Daken BT6 electric fence energiser is suitable for strip grazing and smaller fencing applications for up to 6km's of fence.
The compact BT6 is a short-range energiser that suits strip grazing and small permanent jobs around your property. It has a self-diagnostic ability to tell you if you have a short or that the battery is low and needs to be recharged. A practical and easy to use energiser that is strong, ant and weather proof.

Diagnostic Centre with, energiser OK, Overload, Low battery

Comes with fence red and earth green leads
3 Year Factory Warranty
Designed, Assembled, Tested and Serviced in Australia
  Battery Required:
A 12V Battery is not included with this energizer.
We do sell small low cost 12V 7.2AH Batteries that can be paired with this unit.
The 12V 7.2AH battery will last roughly 5 days before needing a charge. We also sell 20ah batteries that will last roughly 10 days before needing a charge. 
12V Batteries with a larger â€œAHâ€, eg: 70ah (standard size car battery), 100ah or more will allow this unit to run for a number of weeks before requiring a recharge. 
Look after your battery, Keep in a plastic battery box or container to protect it from the weather, and where possible keep it off the ground to stop it from self-discharging.

column4: Qty x 1 MB16 SKU EFJPTE2157 Supplier Code PTE2157
column9:
Over 1000 units sold worldwide!
 
The JVA MB16 Electric Fence IP Energizer® makes animal control a breeze. Its new styling and features include an audible warning if there is a serious fault on the fence and JVA's patented Auto-Sync TM Technology which helps keep your fences safe. 
 
 
This latest version brings the world's first Wi-Fi enabled IOT energizer, and allows the user to monitor and control their energizer from anywhere in the world using any smartphone or tablet. To see this in action, and to try before you buy, please visit our site.
 
Also available as a 150W Solar Kit.
 
See our solution to Exclusion fencing: The Electric Fence Station!
 
For information on how to set up a Wi-Fi fence configuration, click here.
 
Features:
 
 
Can now be monitored and controlled from anywhere in the world from your Android device or iPhone using our free App
 
16J (22J stored) powers up to 160 kilometres of fence*
 
Sleek styling, rugged practical design
 
Mains or 12V Battery operation (Battery not included)
 
Auto-Sync™ Technology for safer fences
 
LCD shows fence voltage, stored energy and battery voltage
 
Power on demand (automatically ramps up power when needed)
 
Bi-Polar or conventional output
 
Reverse battery protection
 
Highly efficient and intelligent digital design
 
UV stable enclosure
 
O-Ring sealed case for ant and moisture protection
 
Designed and manufactured in Australia
 
 * The actual acres or kilometers of fence powered by this energizer depends on your farm fence conditions and therefore varies greatly. The best method to compare energizers is to compare their output energy, in Joules.
 
Package Contents
 
 
MB16 Energizer
 
Battery to Energizer Leads
 
AC Power Adapter
 
Manual/Instructions
 
 
**For connection from the Energizer live terminal to the fence you will need a suitable high voltage cable (not included).
 
Warranty
 
3 year Manufacturer Warranty (excludes lightning damage)
 
 
 
To estimate your solar needs, use our Solar Calculator:
 
 
 
Australian Made

column9:
The Daken 12â€ stand off wires are a unique design that accommodates both plastic, Steely 72222D, Pinlock Y 72200D and the Large Porcelain reel 71500D. They are made from 3.8mm spring steel, the foot design can be twisted onto plain wire, barbed wire or ring lock fences. By crossing the legs of the stand off you lock the reel insulator in place, and if using a Pinlock you take the pressure off the insulator pin. The beauty of this wire is that you can add them where needed, if you are using the porcelain insulator and need to add a couple of extra wires you can add a Pinlock version without having to cut the wire.
Accommodates porcelain reel and Pinlock insulator
Easy to install
Suitable to most fences
Comes in pack of 25

column8: The smart bobbin can be used to replace a broken bobbin by clipping onto the fence wire and into the existing wire stand-off.\n* Use with N-N201, N-N202, N-N203 brackets.
column9:
Description:
 
 
These bobbins are perfect for replacing damaged or broken plastic and porcelain bobbin insulators without having to remove the fence wire! Instead of threading these bobbins over the end of the wire, they can easily be clipped onto the wire where they are needed, then clipped into a wire offset bracket.
See the product photos for a detailed, step-by-step view of how these bobbins attach. Also included is an example of where the Smart bobbin can be used to replace a broken bobbin by clipping onto the fence wire and into the existing wire stand-off.
Note: This listing is for the bobbins only (does not include offsets or corner mount hooks)
 
Features:
 
 
UV protected plastic
 
Quantity: 25 insulators
 
Outer rim diameter (47mm) and inner rim diameter (28mm) 
 
 
Can be used with 225mm Offset, 340mm Offset, or 450mm Offset brackets.

column4: Qty x 25 Locked Insulator SKU EFJSP018-25 Supplier Code SP018
column8:
Locks politape/wire into insulator.
Self-tapping screw for fastening to wooden posts.
Fits poliwire up to 6mm.
Fits politape up to 12mm.
column9:
Most electric fence insulators either have gaps to allow easy insertion and removal of fence wire - leading to wire falling out unless wrapped tightly around the insulator, adding unwanted tension - or they are closed. Having a closed insulator means it will be difficult to perform maintenance on a particular post or insulator without having to disassemble the entire fence. The Locked-Insulator has the security of closed insulators with the ease of service of open insulators. Being able to accept up to 6mm thick wire or up to 12mm wide tape, the Locked-Insulator is suitable for most electric fence installations.

Features:

UV-resistant plastic

Accepts up to 6mm fence wire or 12mm fence tape

Secure locking design

Custom-made screw-in construction makes for easy installation

Quantity: 25 pieces

For more details, a video demonstration can be found here.

column9:
Zon Mark 4 is the most user-friendly propane cannon in the world, full mechanical operation. Suitable for birds and kangaroos.
Approx. 17,000 detonations from a 9KG (20LB) LPG tank
Blast volume up to 125db
Blast volume adjustable by telescopic inner barrel
1-shot device
Interval between shots infinitely adjustable from approx. 45 seconds to approx. 30 minutes.
High reliability piezo electronic ignition detonations.
Very easy to maintain, with only a few moving parts
Very effective and inexpensive.
APPLICATIONS
Agricultural
Crops and fruits orchards damaged by marauding birds can be controlled by strategic placements of ZON Guns. The effective operating radius ranges from 1 to 5 acres, depending upon the shape and topography of the field. 
Commercial-Industrial
Bird hazard and nuisance in critical areas such as airports, seaports, rocket bases, etc, can be controlled with ZON Gun placements. 
Predator and Wildlife Control
Birds (Cockatoos, Ducks), Kangaroos etc.
Documents and Manuals
Zon Mark 4 Operating Instructions Manual

column8: Used to ground electric fence.\nConnect to earth terminal on energiser.
column9:
0.9m Galvanised Steel Earth Stake. This earth stake is suitable for all small energizers up to an MB4.5.
 
Also known as Earth rod, ground stake or ground rod.
 
Electric fence energizers must be earthed to deliver a sufficient shock. An earth is simply some metal in contact with the earth (ground). Larger energizers need better earth systems. Problems with electric fences can be caused by poor earthing, particularly in dry conditions because dry and sandy soil needs more metal in the ground. If your earth is not good enough, put in more earth stakes at 1m intervals and wire them together. Also, using larger earth spikes, driven fully into the ground will be more effective than several shorter spikes.

Pack of 10 posts
 
Overall length: 150cm
 
Easy to install and remove
 
Perfect for temporary electric fence enclosures
 
Suitable for use with Polytape or polywire/rope
 
 
Warranty

column9:
Electric fence swivel cut-out switch. These are typically attached to the first fence-post and wired between the lead-out wire from the Energizer and the start of your fence to easily switch the fence off. They can also be wired into various sections of fence to switch specific sections or paddocks on and off. This can help reduce load on the Energizer while paddocks are not in use, and can help isolate faults (although this is much easier with a JVA Fault Finder!). The perfect accessory for any fence!
 
 
Features:
 
 
Simple to install - simply mounts to a post or wall using the supplied screws
 
Uses wing-nuts to easily fasten lead-out and fence wire to the switch contacts
 
UV protected

column8: Spark gap type lightning arrestor. Protects your energiser from Lightning Strikes. \nAdjustable spark gap. \nWeather proof enclosure.

Description:
 
Featuring an adjustable arc gap, this unique, V-shaped JVA Electric Fence Lightning Diverter is ideal for using to protect electric fence Energizers which power permanent electric fences. 
 
Features:
 
 
Easy to install between the fence and the Energizer
 
Conducts lightning current to the earth to protect the Energizer
 
Can be installed outdoors
 
Weather and ant resistant
 
Choke and Arc gap built into one diverter
 
Fence terminals are covered for safety
 
Adjustable Arc Gap
 
Added insulation plate for mounting on a metal wall
 
 
Note:

column4: Qty x 1 Multi-stage Lightning Diverter SKU EFJPTE0054P Supplier Code PTE0054P
column8: Robust multi-stage lightning diverter.\nProtects energiser from lightning strikes.\nContains RFI filter to aid in reducing electrical interference.
column9:
Simple to fit and proven effective in the field over many years this device is cheap insurance for any electric fence Energizer. 
 
 
Easy to fit, completely sealed against the elements, this device is a true multi-stage lightning diverter, not just a cheap spark gap! 
JVA model number: PTE0054
Note: Not suitable for Energizers with rated output over 25 Joules.
 
Features:
 
 
Easy to install
 
Cheap and reliable way to protect your Energizer
 
Contains an RFI filter to aid in reducing the electrical interference that can cause a ticking noise on telephones and inhibit the use of the Internet.
 
 
Warranty
 
A three year warranty protects you from the cost of Energizer repair should the diverter fail or be hit by a damaging surge of lightning (registration of the Energizer to be protected is required).

column4: Qty x 1 Dual Chanel Lightning Diverter SKU EFJPTE0231 Supplier Code PTE0231
column8:
Protect energiser from Lightning Strikes.
Protects feed and return wires on Z-Series energisers.
Withstand surges of up to 2000 amps. 
Indoor mounting only!
column9:
The JVA Dual Channel Lightning Diverter is the must have device when installing Z-Series Energizers in lightning prone areas. It provides protection for the Energizer on both the Feed and Return fence wires ensuring a lightning strike on, or near the fence, is safely diverted to Earth. Its two stage protection can withstand a lightning surge of up to 2000 Amps limiting the voltage to the Energizer to an acceptable 15kV.
 
 
Features:
 
 
Feed and Return wiring protection
 
Affordable sacrificial security component
 
One Diverter required for most installations
 
Provides a highly visible indication of a lightning surge
 
Large sturdy terminals for solid under-gate wiring
 
 
NOTE: This product is not waterproof, it must be mounted indoors on an insulated backing board or wall.

column4: Qty x 1 JVA Fault Finder  SKU EFJPTE0129 Supplier Code PTE0129
column8: One touch operation.\nClear display showing voltage and current.\nFind faults fast with fault direction indicators.
column9:
The JVA Electric Fence Fault Finder® makes finding shorts on electric fence as easy as following an arrow. It is also known as an Electric Fence Power Probe®. Designed and Manufactured in Australia by the inventors and original manufacturer Pakton Technologies.
 
 
Features:
 
 
Water proof design 
 
Integrated (removable) belt clip 
 
Long lasting battery 
 
Ergonomic case design 
 
Fingers are further away from high voltage 
 
Bright red LED direction arrows 
 
One touch operation - Simple to use 
 
Clear indications of the direction of the fault 
 
Digital readout which shows fence voltage and current 
 
No wires, no clips means no tangles, no shocks! 
 
Standard easy to find 9V battery 
 
Australian made by the inventor of directional fault finders 
 
Pocket size - easy to carry 
 
Displays direction to a "high load" fault, not just current flow 
 
Will take you right to the fault, not leave you metres short
 
 
Questions? Queries? Check our Fault finder FAQ here
 
Warranty
 
JVA Fault Finders are covered under a 3 year manufacturer's warranty.
 
 
 
 
 Also available as a component of the JVA Fault Finder Accessory Kit.

The JVA Electric Fence Fault Finder® makes finding shorts on electric fence as easy as following an arrow. It is also known as an Electric Fence Power Probe®. Designed and Manufactured in Australia by the inventors and original manufacturer Pakton Technologies.
 
 
This Kit comes with a handy, soft carry pouch, and pair of short out leads to make fixing faults easier and safer!
 
Features:
 
 
Water proof design 
 
Long lasting 9v battery 
 
Ergonomic case design with integrated (removable) belt clip
 
One touch operation - Safe and simple to use 
 
 
Clear indications of the direction of the fault 
 
Digital readout which shows fence voltage and current 
 
Australian made by the inventor of directional fault finders 
 
 
Pocket size - easy to carry 
 
Displays direction to a "high load" fault, not just current flow 
 
Will take you right to the fault, not leave you metres short
 
 
Package Includes:
 
 
JVA Electric Fence Fault Finder
 
Short-out Leads
 
Carry Pouch
 
 
Warranty
 
JVA Fault Finders are covered under a 3 year manufacturer's warranty.

*This product is undergoing an upgrade, as we run out of old stock you will begin to receive the new Version 2*

The Pulsar is an electric fence indicator light. Also known as a flasher or night light it is connected to the live and earth wires and emits a bright flash with each fence pulse. Except this one is actually bright enough to see plainly in day light. Made with seven high intensity LEDs the Pulsar will let you know at a glance that the fence is on or off.  


Incredibly helpful if you install it by your gate so you can check your fence as you drive through.

See Pictures for wiring diagram - can be attached using crimps, wire clamps, or simply by twisting the wires around the fence wire.

Features:
Seven high intensity LEDs - bright and extremely long life
Waterproof
Rugged - it stands up to the challenge of harsh environments!
Simple connection using stainless wire twists
Please note: These lights are not recommended for Energizers with less than 1.0 Joules output.

column4: Qty x 1 ZM1 Monitor SKU EFJPTE0202 Supplier Code PTE0202
column8:
Single zone electric fence monitor. 
Can be configured as a start of fence power monitor, or an end of fence voltage monitor. 
Part of the JVA Z-series. 
Works with keypads and Perimeter Patrol.
column9:
The JVA ZM1 is designed to be coupled with any standard electric fence Energizer to power and monitor an electric fence. The ZM1 brings electric fences into the 21st century. Applications include perimeter security, zoos,sanctuaries and protection of valuable animals such as thoroughbreds. The ZM1 allows you to remotely control your electric fence from:
 
 
 
Your house using the optional LCD keypad or Touch Keypad
 
Your PC using Perimeter Patrol – with e-mailed alarms
 
Anywhere in the world using the internet
 
 
Features:
 
 
Start or end of fence monitoring
 
Anti-bridging mode – alarms on sudden change in fence load
 
Monitors ground voltage, fence voltage and fence current
 
Control and program via LCD keypad or Touch Keypad
 
Monitor via PC (using Perimeter Patrol software)
 
Remote on/off or Key switch
 
Siren and Strobe switched 12V DC outputs
 
3 Form C relays with many programmable functions
 
Built in charger and space for a 12V 7.2aH backup battery
 
Run from 16Vac or 12Vdc external source
 
 
Notes
 
 
 Battery not included (COB004) 
 
16Vac plug pack not included (COP002) 
 
 
 
 
Warranty
 
3 Year Manufacturer Warranty (excluding lightning damage)

column4: Qty x 1 ZM20 SKU EFJPTE0213 Supplier Code PTE0213
column8:
Single zone, 20 sector electric fence monitor. 
Monitors a zone of electric fence and can report a fault in any sector. 
Part of the JVA Z-series. 
Works with keypads and Perimeter Patrol.
column9:
The JVA ZM20 is designed to be coupled with any standard electric fence Energizer to power and monitor a perimeter security electric fence. In addition to the features of the ZM1 the ZM20 can be programmed to determine the position of a fault on the fence. Up to 20 different sectors within 1 zone can be differentiated. The ZM20 powers both “ends” of the fence and determines the position of a fault using digital signal processing.
 
 
Features:
 
 
2 to 20 Programmable Sectors
 
Reports the fault position (LCD and data output)
 
Cut or bridge alarm on sudden reduction in current
 
Monitors ground voltage, fence voltage and fence currents
 
Control and program via LCD keypad or Touch keypad
 
Monitor via PC (using Perimeter Patrol software)
 
2 dry contact control inputs
 
Siren and Strobe switched 12V DC outputs
 
3 form C relays with many programmable functions
 
Built in charger and space for a 12V 7.2aH backup battery
 
Run from 16Vac or 12Vdc external source
 
Anywhere in the world using the Internet
 
 
Notes
 
 
Battery not included (COB004) 
 
16Vac plug pack not included (COP002) 
 
 
*The actual acres or kilometers of fence powered by this Energizer depends on your farm fence conditions and therefore varies greatly. The best method to compare energizers is to compare their output energy, in Joules. 
 
Warranty
 
3 Year Manufacturer Warranty (excluding lightning damage)

column8:
Four zone ELV (Extreme Low Voltage) electric fence energiser/monitor. 
Part of the JVA Z-series. 
Monitors four low voltage zones and can report a fault each zone. 
Works with keypads and Perimeter Patrol.
* Recommend installing with PTE0340
column9:
The JVA ZLM4 is a 4 zone low voltage electric fence monitor. The ZLM4 may be used by itself or in conjunction with a number of high voltage security electric fence Energizers. The ZLM4 monitors up to 4 loops of fence wire, each up to several hundred meters long, to detect someone tampering with the fence by cutting or shorting the wires using intrinsically safe, isolated Extra-Low Voltage (ELV) DC.
 
 
Features:
 
 
Monitors using safe 50V DC pulses
 
Can be used to split a single security electric fence zone into up to 4 low voltage zones
 
4 detection modes
 
LCD display for advanced visual feedback on unit monitoring
 
Control and program via LCD keypad or Touch keypad
 
Monitor via PC[1] (using Perimeter Patrol software)
 
Powered from 16Vac or 12V DC external source
 
In built battery charger
 
Siren and Strobe switched 12V DC outputs
 
2 control inputs
 
4 form C relay outputs with many programmable functions
 
 
Notes
 
 
 Battery not included (COB004) 
 
16Vac plug pack not included (COP002)

column4: Qty x 1 Multi Output Fence Monitor SKU EFJPTE0705 Supplier Code PTE0705
column8:
Provides an interface between Fence Voltage for other monitoring systems.
Delivers 0-10V, RS232 and Relay contact outputs. 
Powered from 12V. 
Used in SCADA and farm monitoring systems.
column9:
Description:
 
The PTE0705 Electric Fence Monitor is designed to allow the voltage on an electric fence to be integrated into another system. When an electric fence voltage is connected to the input terminals, this monitor will deliver a reading of the peak fence voltage in a number of useful formats. These can be connected to SCADA equipment, weather monitoring devices or a remote telemetry unit (RTU) to gather and return electric fence voltage.
 
Features:
 
 
Monitors the peak pulse voltage from any electric fence*
 
12V supply with reverse polarity protection
 
0-10V Analogue output
 
RS232 serial output
 
LED bar graph
 
Form C relay with programmable alarm level
 
IP65 weatherproof wall-mountable enclosure
 
 
Warranty
 
3 year Manufacturer Warranty (excludes lightning damage)
 
* The electric fence energizer must be rated at greater than 0.2J (2km) for an accurate reading.

column4: Qty x 1 IP Monitor SKU EFJPTE2603 Supplier Code PTE2603
column8: IP Enabled (Wi-Fi) Electric Fence.\nMonitor with inbuilt EHT switch.\nControlled using free IP energiser Controller App .
column9:
The JVA IP Monitor is an internet-connected electric fence monitor. Using our free IP Energizer Controller app, it allows you to check your electric fence from anywhere in the world. You can also get alerts if the fence voltage or current go beyond your configurable thresholds. Models containing a high voltage relay also allow you to control the fence, switching it on or off remotely. It works with any energizer and uses built-in Wi-Fi technology to make connection a breeze.
 
The JVA IP Monitor is available in two options, the non relay version (IPM3) can monitor the fence, whereas the relay version (IPM1) can monitor and control the fence remotely. 
 
All versions will report the fence voltage and the current flowing through the monitor.
 
For information on how to set up the Wi-Fi, click here.
 
Features:
 
 
Mains or 12V Battery operation
 
Built-in Wi-Fi for direct internet connection
 
Can use 3G/4G cellular network with a separate modem/hotspot (not included)
 
High power internal relay (IPM1 model)
 
Works with any energizer up to 36J*
 
Start-of-fence or end-of-fence monitoring
 
Can break a large fence system into separately controlled and monitored zones
 
UV stable enclosure 
 
O-ring sealed case for ant and moisture protection
 
IP Energizer Controller app available for iPhone and Android 
 
Designed and manufactured in Australia
 
 
*NOTE: Warranty void if used with energizers rated over 36J

column8:
9" Touch Screen Keypad in metal frame.
Quick and intuitive  Z- Range energiser and Monitor Programming.

Onboard event log.
Emailed alarm notifications.
column9:
The JVA Touch Keypad is the most intuitive keypad for the setup, control and monitoring of all Z series security energizers and monitors. Get your site set-up quickly by programming your devices via the touch screen interface. Quickly arm or disarm all or individual zones via pin protected buttons. The fluid user interface is updated in real time providing peace of mind at a glance. The always persistent top bar keeps you informed of any alarms and displays a pulse animation in time with the energizers. Email notifications can be configured to alert you of every alarm as and when they occur. View the onboard log of each and every user authenticated action or alarm.
 
 
Features:
 
 
Quick and intuitive Energizer and monitor programming in just a few presses
 
Fast and fluid user interface – similar to that of your phone or tablet
 
Check the status at a glance with Energizer pulse animations and colour coded fence conditions, updated in real time
 
Onboard event log records every alarm, arm, and disarm along with the user that authorized it
 
Receive immediate email notifications on alarm
 
Size (Height x Width x Depth): 217mm x 287mm x 20mm
 
9" diagonal screen width
 
 
Package Contents
 
 
PTE0233 Touch Keypad
 
Power Supply
 
Mounting instructions
 
Mounting screws
 
Screen protector
 
Protective metal wall-mount frame

12 Month Manufacturer Warranty

column8:
Control, monitor and program any Z-Series energiser and Monitor.

Menu driven interface.
column9:
The JVA 4-Line LCD Keypad is an integral component in the JVA Security Electric Fence product range. Providing a centralised interface between the Customer and their Perimeter Security Solution; it displays the current condition of each security device connected and can draw attention to adverse fence conditions. The keypad is used to control individual fence Energizers, Monitors or the entire site. The Customer has access to all of these features via a Menu Driven system or by entering key sequences. Security Installers also use the keypad to configure the JVA Security devices to the customer’s needs.
 
 
Features:
 
 
Control, monitor and program any Z-Series device
 
Displays Armed / Disarmed status and any trouble or alarm
 
Device screen displays fence voltages and conditions
 
Visual and Audible indication of alarm and trouble events
 
Menu driven interface
 
4-line Backlit LCD Display
 
Quick Arm/Disarm keys
 
500 entry Event Log with accurate Date and Time information
 
1 - 14 energizers can be controlled from one Keypad;
 
1 - 3 keypads can control one energizer
 
 
Warranty
 
3 Year Manufacturer Warranty (excludes lightning damage)

column9:
The JVA Wi-Fi Gateway allows for wireless communication between the JVA Cloud Router and a group of Z-series energizers, monitors, and accessories, enabling remote access and monitoring of all of your devices from your smart phone or PC. This Gateway features an intelligent bandwidth-conserving protocol that only updates your device information if there are any changes to the connected energizer network, significantly reducing the Gateway’s data consumption.
 
Features:
 
 
Mounts inside the Energizer enclosure
 
Connects up to 15 JVA Z-series Energizers, monitors and accessories
 
 Allows monitoring and control of your site from anywhere in the world with the Cloud Router app*
 
Conserves bandwidth by only sending new information to the Cloud Router, ensuring minimum data use
 
Cloud router can be configured to send alerts via SMS, Email or Facebook messenger **
 
Enables energizer network history logging with the Cloud Router, showing exactly what happened, when, and who authorized it
 
 
* requires a Wi-fi connection, which may be via a GSM Hotspot.
 
** Cloud Router Pro is required for alerts and has a monthly fee
 
Check our website for an easy setup guide!
 
Warranty
 3 Year Manufacturer Warranty (excluding lightning damage)

column9:
The JVA Perimeter Patrol Interface provides Ethernet connectivity for the Z-Series Energizers and monitors. On the Keypad bus port it connects to 1 - 14 Z-Series devices. On the TCP/IP port it connects over LAN or WAN to a PC running Perimeter Patrol. By using multiple TCP/IP interface boards a system can be expanded to more than 100 zones. This interface handles pulse synchronisation for all connected Energizers. HLI code and an SDK are also available to enable integration into other systems.
 
Features:
 
 
 
Two ports, Keypad bus (screw terminals) and Ethernet (RJ45)
 
Translates serial data to TCP/IP
 
Powered from the Z-Series Energizer Keypad bus
 
May be placed inside a Z-Series Enclosure
 
 
Warranty

column9:
The JVA Ethernet GPIO Board adds even more functionality to the JVA Perimeter Alarm System. It provides stand alone inputs and outputs to easily integrate external equipment into the Perimeter Patrol System. The inputs can monitor either Digital or Analogue devices such as temperature sensors, pressure sensors and water level indicators, while the outputs can be used to turn on security lighting, sirens or water pumps. Finally, the GPIO board can be configured to provide a combination of Perimeter Patrol Outputs and Energizer Expansion Outputs on the one board for greater flexibility. The Ethernet GPIO board also provides Ethernet connectivity between Perimeter Patrol and up-to 14 Z-Series Energizers or Monitors.

Features:

20W Solar panel

12A Solar regulator included

Connects to any 12V lead acid battery*

Sturdy aluminium construction

No tools required

No assembly required

Quick simple set-up

3 year warranty

* JVA recommends an old car battery. Re-use, reduce, recycle!

Warranty

Also available as a kit with the MB1.5 Energizer.

To estimate your solar needs, use our Solar Calculator:

column8: 50W Solar Kit for MB3, MB4.5, Z14, Z14R or Z14E energisers.\nIncludes solar regulator.\nPost mountable.
column9:
The JVA 50W Solar Bundle / Kit is a quick, easy way to provide power to your JVA MBx series Energizer. Simply unfold and secure the panel to a pole using the provided U-Bolts, tighten the bolts, attach a suitable sized 12V lead acid battery, and connect to your JVA MB3 or MB4.5 Energizer. Free power from the sun will keep your electric fence running 24/7. For help on selecting the correct sized battery see our Solar Calculator. If you live in Tasmania or NZ please check the calculator before using this with a MB4.5.
 
This Solar kit can also be used to charge a 12V Lead Acid battery for any purpose where the 12V power consumption is approximately 5W continuous or less. May be suitable for other manufacturers 12V power electric fence energizers rated up to 4.5J output, or 45km.
 
Features:
 
 
50W Solar Panel
 
Sturdy aluminium bracket
 
PTE3004 Solar Regulator
 
Wired up ready to plug into the energizer and battery
 
Quick easy set-up directions included
 
3 year warranty
 
 
 
You will need a MB3.0 or MB4.5 Energizer.
 
Warranty
 
3 year Manufacturer Warranty (excludes battery and lightning damage)
 
 
 
Can also be purchased as a kit with the MB3 or MB4.5 Energizer.
 
To estimate your solar needs, use our Solar Calculator:

column8: BT12 Energiser + 10W Pre-Mounted Panel, Battery Not Included
column9:
Overview:
Daken solar powered energisers are ideal for remote locations or where mains power is not readily accessible. Ideal for strip grazing, temporary fencing and for permanent placement.
Specification: 
The Daken 12km solar electric fence kit is a system packaged ready to go that just requires a battery for permanent fencing applications. Suitable for multi wire fences up to 12km. The system incorporates a BT12 12KM energiser, quality crystalline 10Watt universal Solar Panel, and Solar Mount.  The universal solar mount can be screwed on to wooden posts or wired onto steel posts. 
Quick specs
Range up to 12km multi wire fence
Power 1.2 Stored Joules
Diagnostic Centre with, energiser OK, Overload, Low battery
Quality Crystalline 10watt Solar Panel
Approx 8kv Output Energiser
Universal Solar Mount
3 Year Factory Energiser Warranty
Designed, Assembled, Tested and Serviced by us in Australia 
Battery Recommendation:
You will require a 12Volt (13.8Volt) battery to operate this BT12. 
(BATTERY NOT INCLUDED IN THIS KIT)
A standard automotive battery is will be more than sufficient.
The Daken 12V 17AH battery P/N: 70405D is perfectly suited to this Solar system. 
Look after your battery, Keep in a plastic battery box or container to protect it from the weather, and where possible keep it off the ground to stop it from self-discharging.
Documents and Manuals
12km Solar Kit Manual
Daken Installation manual

column4: Qty x 1 20W Wifi Anywhere™ Kit SKU EFJPTE2700 Supplier Code PTE2700
column8: 20w Solar Kit with Wifi Anywhere™.\nBuilt in Wi-Fi through third party 3G/4G sim.\nPost mountable.
column9:
If your problem is getting a Wi-Fi connection in the middle of nowhere, the JVA Solar Wi-Fi Access Point (SWAP) is the answer. The PTE2700 is part of JVA’s Wi-Fi Anywhere™ product range. The USB Modem in the PTE2700 uses a standard SIM card to produce Wi-Fi from cellular networks [1] like Telstra’s 4G. Use it to create a Wi-Fi “hotspot” where ever you need it. This could be; in a paddock, near a gate or beside your shed. This can be used to connect devices like JVA IP Energizers® to the Internet. Other devices such as IP Cameras, Automatic Gates, Weather Stations, Pumps, Water monitors and Alarm systems can also be connected. Since the SWAP is solar powered, it is free to run, and can be placed anywhere within 3G/4G cell phone coverage. It can even operate in marginal signal areas with the addition of a larger antenna [2].
 
 
Features:
 
 
Includes $5 prepaid SIM
 
Simply safe and easy to setup
 
Small size makes it great for portable systems
 
12V Battery Required [3] 
 
Reverse battery protection
 
Highly efficient and intelligent digital circuit
 
Battery level indicator
 
20W solar panel works throughout Australia
 
UV stable enclosure
 
Ant and moisture protection
 
 
[1] Compatible with any Australian cellular operator, only data connection is required
 [2] Small external cellular antenna included (3G/4G)
 [3] Minimum battery size 25Ah for Lead-Acid 18Ah for Lithium Iron
 
Warranty
 
3 year Manufacturer Warranty (excludes lightning damage)
 
Also available as a JVA Solar Electric Fence Monitor

column9:
This kit combines the MB8 Energizer with our 100W solar panel, bracket and regulator. Making it a "ready to go" solar electric fence power solution. All you need to add is a 12V lead acid battery and a post or pole to mount it on.

The JVA MB8 Electric Fence IP Energizer® makes animal control a breeze.  Its new styling and features include an audible warning if there is a  serious fault on the fence and JVA's patented Auto-Sync TM Technology  which helps keep your fences safe. 

This latest revision brings the world's first Wi-Fi enabled IOT energizer, and allows the user to monitor and control their energizer from anywhere in the world using a Smart phone (Android or Apple). To see this in action, and to try before you buy, please visit our site.

If you live in Victoria, Tasmania, or New Zealand, check our Solar Calculator for suitability in your region.

Want something even larger? See our solution to Exclusion fencing: The Electric Fence Station!

MB8 Features:
Can now be monitored and controlled from anywhere in the world from your Android phone
8 Joules powers up to 80 kilometres of fence.*
Sleek styling, rugged practical design
Mains or 12V Battery operation (battery not included)
Auto-Sync™ Technology for safer fences
LCD shows fence voltage, stored energy and battery voltage
Power on demand (automatically ramps up power when needed)
Bi-Polar or conventional output
Reverse battery protection
Highly efficient and intelligent digital design
UV stable enclosure
O-Ring sealed case for ant and moisture protection
Designed and manufactured in Australia
Solar Kit Features:
100W Solar Panel
Sturdy aluminium bracket
PTE3004 Solar Regulator
Wired up ready to plug into the energizer and battery
Quick easy set-up directions included
* The actual acres or kilometers of fence powered  by this energizer depends on your farm fence conditions and therefore  varies greatly.  The best method to compare energizers is to compare their output energy, in Joules.
 

**For connection from the Energizer live terminal to the fence you will need a suitable high voltage cable (not included).

 

Warranty
3 year Manufacturer Warranty (excludes lightning damage)

The JVA MB16 Mains/Battery Electric Fence IP Energizer® WiFi and 4G Kit is a complete solution for getting your IP Energizer® up and running. We provide a 4G USB Modem pre-configured to the IP Energizer® and a $5 ALDI starter pack SIM card. Connect the IP energizer® to your fence and mount the 4G USB Modem nearby*.  You will need to register the Aldi SIM card. We suggest using the $15 PAYG plan, it will last about a year. We provide a USB power solution for 240V mains.

*Note: The 4G USB Modem is not waterproof.

The JVA MB16 Electric Fence IP Energizer®  is one of JVA's world's first Wi-Fi enabled IOT energizers. It allows you to monitor and control your electric fence energizer from anywhere in the world using any smartphone or tablet. To see this in action, and to try before you buy, please visit our site.

The MB16 also has an audible warning if there is a  serious fault on the fence and contains JVA's patented Auto-Sync TM Technology which helps keep your fences safe.

Battery to Energizer Leads

Manual/Instructions

column9:
The JVA Electric Fence Station (PTE2500A) is an all-in-one, solar powered fence energizer and monitor solution for up to 20km of boundary fence or a lot more internal fencing. It will power and monitor two sections of fence, detect faults and notify you directly to your mobile phone by SMS or email. This product monitors the feed voltage and current and detects distant faults using our patented Distant Fault Detection (DFD)™ system on very long fences. With JVA’s Cloud Router system™, you can turn the fences on or off individually, and check their voltage at any time directly from your phone. A powerful 25 Joule (output) Jumbo Energizer provides enough punch to keep stock in and feral or wild animals out. Best of all, it comes with everything you need to hook it up – you just need a 60mm round pole in the ground.
 
Get peace of mind that your fence is working, day and night, with the latest from JVA.
 
* This station requires two 100ah 12V lead acid batteries (COB005), you can choose to add these to the order or supply your own. Alternatively talk to us about a LiFePo battery. 
 
* Please note that, due to the fence station's size, free shipping is NOT offered on this product.
 
* The actual acres or kilometers of fence powered by this Energizer depends on your farm fence conditions and therefore varies greatly. The best method to compare energizers is to compare their output energy, in Joules.

Powers and monitors two 10km sections of boundary fence 
 
Lightning protection included
 
315W solar panel with mounting bracket
 
20A MPPT Solar regulator 
 
JMB25 JVA ZM2 energiser / monitor
 
Cellular Gateway works with any mobile network
 
 Cloud Router® remote monitoring and control
 
Check the fence status from anywhere in the world
 
Get notified directly if a fault occurs
 
Waterproof cabinet
 
Pre-wired with solar and battery leads
 
Simple connection instructions

Circuit breakers

Complete instructions, stored in-cabinet

Mounting Pole

The JVA Z14 is a single zone security electric fence Energizer purpose built for control and monitoring of perimeter security electric fences. It can meet all of the requirements from basic residential to fully integrated high profile installations. The Z14 can be programmed and controlled using the optional LCD keypad or Touch keypad. It can also be networked with other Z Range Energizers to form a pulse synchronized group for larger sites which require multiple zones.
 
Features:
 
 
Safe but effective deterrent, high voltage output
 
High and low power modes
 
Built in charger and space for a 12V 7.2aH backup battery
 
Supports Bi-Polar or conventional fence wiring
 
Alarms on fence short or open circuit
 
Control and programming via LCD keypad or Touch keypad
 
Large number of programmable options
 
Monitor via PC (using Perimeter Patrol software)
 
2 control inputs
 
2 switched 12V DC outputs (Siren and Strobe)
 
 
Notes
 
 
12V 7ah battery is not included, but is required (COB004)

Responsive energiser designed to protect Horses.

column9:
The JVA Z14E is an electric fence energizer designed specifically for equine use. 
 
We know that sometimes horses can spook and get tangled in fence wires, because of this the Z14E is programmed to sense a fence fault and drop to low power mode. In low power mode the pulse energy drops to a level just high enough to detect the fence condition; when the energizer senses that the fault has been removed, then it will resume high power mode. 
 
The Z14E is part of the JVA Z series of security products. As such it can be connected to any of the Z series accessories such as Keypads and Cloud Router gateways for advanced control and offsite monitoring. 
 
The Z14E comes with a power supply (COP002). A 12V 7.5 ah battery (COB004) is recommended to provide backup power to run the energiser for up to 8 hours during a mains power failure.
 
Features:
 • Safe, secure, and reactive to protect high value animals
• High and low power modes
• Automatically switches to between low and high power to
minimise stress should an animal become entangled
• Tested and approved to AS/NZS60335.2.76
• Built in charger and space for a 12V 7.2aH backup battery
• Alarms on fence short or open circuit (correct fence wiring is required)
• Large number of programmable options (keypad required)
• Remote control and monitoring via Cloud Router (a gateway is required)
